In the Empire, the most loyal, talented and (most importantly) merciless soldiers are granted the honor of undergoing special training to serve in more advanced, specialized divisions of the Imperial Military. These soldiers are among those elite few to be offered this opportunity. 

Equipped with more advanced weapons and armor, and authorized to act more independently than their trooper brethren, it is their job to scout out the enemy for weaknesses, and disrupt the enemy command structure. 

Of course, as only those who view the lives of others as meaningless are accepted into such roles, they'll gladly turn their rifles on just about any target in their considerable ranges, civilian or military.

This mountain of walking biomass wears some of the heaviest armors created among the Mandalorians.  A lifetime of training, and sheer determination allow this walking fortress to advance, and it will take some heavy ordinance to change their mind.

To a Mandalorian, war is a way of life.  They worship the very idea of war and believe that to wage it is to commune with the Divine.  To battle is the ultimate form of worship, and they devote their entire lives to this act.

The Baar'ur is a necessity to any Mandalorian Clain.  To a Mandalorian, war is a way of life.  They worship the very idea of war and believe that to wage it is to commune with the Divine.  To battle is the ultimate form of worship, and they devote their entire lives to this act.  The Baar'ur exists to ensure that the rest of their clan lives as long as possible.
